sentence: This election saw the peak of the Australian Democrats ' popularity under Janine Haines, and a Greens Western Australia candidate won a seat in the Australian Senate for the first time - although the successful candidate, Jo Vallentine, was already a two-term senator, having previously won a seat for the Nuclear Disarmament Party at the 1984 Australian federal election, and the Vallentine Peace Group at the 1987 election.
